        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>Anic</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Faust</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Albin</abbr><ex>us</ex></expan> Basilius <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ir</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>larissimus</ex></expan> </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> et <expan><abbr>inl</abbr><ex>ustris</ex></expan> ex <expan><abbr>com</abbr><ex>ite</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>dom</abbr><ex>esticorum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pat</abbr><ex>ricius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>cons</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>ord</abbr><ex>inarius</ex></expan> </ab></div><div n="3" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> bono rei public<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>e</abbr></expan> et iterum
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Die beiden Paneele des Diptychons befinden sich heute getrennt voneinander in Florenz (Mus. Naz. del Bargello: erster Teil der Inschrift, Maße wie angegeben) und Mailand (Castello Sforzesco: zweiter und dritter Teil der Inschrift, Maße 19,9 cm x 12,4 cm). Datierung Volbach: 480 n. Chr. aus stilistischen Gründen.</p>
            </div>
